HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 1576
By Sparks
A RESOLUTION to honor and commend Stevie Ivens, 2026
Valedictorian of Smyrna High School.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that the members of this General Assembly should pause to pay
tribute to those students in our State who, through their natural abilities and unwavering pursuit
of academic excellence, have distinguished themselves in the classroom; and
WHEREAS, Stevie Ivens is one such individual, who has been named Valedictorian of
the 2026 graduating class at Smyrna High School; and
WHEREAS, through dedication to her studies, careful recollection of vast amounts of
data, composure through her examinations, and her steadfast commitment of time and talent,
Ms. Ivens has achieved a remarkable academic feat and joined the ranks of the brightest and
most notable students in Tennessee and our country; and
WHEREAS, in her educational career, Ms. Ivens has maintained an exemplary grade
point average while participating in a number of extracurricular activities, including National
Honor Society, Beta Club, Student Council, and FCCLA, and working as a student volunteer for
the Rocky Ford Elementary School library, mentor to Rocky Fork Middle School students, and
volunteer reader for elementary school events; and
WHEREAS, Stevie Ivens has earned several prestigious awards and honors, including
the Advanced Honors English II Award, the Advanced Placement Precalculus Award, and the
Middle Tennessee State University Centennial Scholarship; and
WHEREAS, her intellectual aptitude and ambition most certainly bode well for her future
endeavors; and
HJR1576
018483
- 1 -

WHEREAS, Ms. Ivens's noteworthy achievement is a tremendous source of pride for her
parents, Stephen and Brandi Ivens; her siblings, Raley, Kinsey, and Karly; her school; and her
community; and
WHEREAS, Stevie Ivens's dedication to excellence is clearly deserving of the respect,
admiration, and commendation of this General Assembly; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we honor and commend the 2026 Smyrna High School Valedictorian,
Stevie Ivens, salute her impressive academic achievement, and extend to her our best wishes
for a happy, successful future.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
